cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with game theory and complexity theory, which are both covered by cs.GT (Game Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of logarithmic-size strategies suggests a connection to data structures, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the mention of small circuits and algorithms suggests a connection to information theory, which is covered by cs.IT (Information Theory).
